Bahrain has passed a decree approvingthe establishment of the country's first stock exchange, theGulf News Agency reported.    The decree placed responsibilty for the stock exchange withthe Ministry of Commerce and Agriculture.    There was no indication when the exchange will open.    Banking sources said government officials are finalisingdetails of a building to house the exchange.    Stock trading in Bahrain is currently conducted via atelephone market. Reuter&#3;